      "repair_reason": "- No ClawSweeper repair lane is needed; the next action is maintainer merge handling after final checks and explicit acceptance of the auth-provider compatibility tradeoff.; Cleared: No concrete security or supply-chain regression was found; the auth-sensitive changes avoid persisting raw Keychain references and add ownership checks around Claude OAuth history routing. (sha=99c6c7ac8e82649582f0415ab0e3068ba7450e96)",
      "review_summary": "The PR isolates Claude OAuth usage in CLI runtime from delegated Claude CLI refresh and version-detection subprocesses, preserves app-initiated repair behavior, adds Claude web deadline handling, and scopes OAuth plan history by Keychain credential identity.\n\nReproducibility: yes. source inspection shows current main can delegate Claude OAuth refresh in CLI runtime and then run Claude version detection after OAuth results. I did not run live Waybar, Claude CLI, OAuth, or Keychain probes because repository policy avoids real account prompts unless explicitly requested.",
